General Rule of Thumb:

Most meteor showers radiate from the east in the hours just after sunset, and climb higher in the sky as night deepens. So:

Look EAST, then upwards and slightly to the left or right, depending on your hemisphere and the showers radiant point.

For Tonight Specifically (July 28):

  • Delta Aquariids:
